title.narrative: To help city governments provide better living standards for the poor, and to evaluate the results of UK support.

description.narrative: This activity (To help city governments provide better living standards for the poor, and to evaluate the results of UK support.) is a component of Madhya Pradesh Urban Infrastructure Investment Project reported by FCDO, with a funding type of 'Procurement of Services' and a budget of £6,921,998. This component benefits India, and works in the following sector(s): Urban development and management. , with the following implementing partners: ICF Consulting Services Ltd, PwC, Social Development Direct Limited, World Resources Institute. The start date is 01-01-2013 and the end date is 31-12-2015.
